frameDefinitions: An implicit cognizer judges that a particular State_of_affairs for which a Protagonist is responsible is socially unacceptable.
In this frame either a Stimulus brings about a particular emotion or experience in the Experiencer or  saliently fails to bring about a particular experience.
In this frame a Profiled_item is higher that its Standard_item on a scale with respect to some Attribute.

The words in this frame describe situations in which the Perpetrator secretly takes Goods into or out of a country or other area which are prohibited by law or on which one has not paid the required duty.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
The Behavior of an Evaluee is described in terms of the reaction it deserves from somebody, such as praise, blame or admiration.
frameExamples: He called it a <t>disgraceful</t> situation. INI
Notices for the Shield Theater's production of Macbeth <t>surpassed</t> all previous reviews .
It was <t>honorable</t> of you to help that person.
listRoleDefinitions: The entity or event which brings disgrace upon the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
The person or organization responsible for the occurrence of the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen>.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the object or event which brings about the emotion in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The role <fen>Standard_item</fen> denotes the entities that are exceeded by the <fen>Item</fen> with regard to the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The <fen>Profiled_item</fen> is the entity that is located closest to the end of the scale evoked by some <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The <fen>Attribute</fen> is a property that evokes a scale along which the <fen>Item</fen> is located closer to one extreme in  comparison to the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The <fen>Standard_attribute</fen> is used when the standard is a specific value on  a scale.
The <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen> is a particular value on a scale which is being compared to an <fen>Attribute</fen> or <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Item</fen> is higher on the scale than the <fen>Standard</fen>.
This is the person (or other agent) that illegally takes the goods into or out of a country.
The role Goods is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be illegally taken into our out of a country.
The source is the location the goods occupy initially before change of location.
The path refers to (a part of the) ground the Goods travel over or to a landmark the Goods travel by.
Goal is the location the Goods end up in.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
The <fen>Behavior</fen> of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged as worthy of a particular reaction.
This role indicates the <fen>Behavior</fen> on which the assessment of praiseworthiness is based.
listRoleExamples: You will soon learn the penalty for your disgraceful <fex>conduct</fex>.
It is disgraceful <fex>to our Public Works Department</fex>.
In her time, she outstripped <fex>most politician in the country</fex>.
<fex>The buildings</fex> were outstripped in beauty and grace many years ago.
The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
It was commendable <fex>of Lisa</fex> to give so much to charity.
